same ind as  XC371133. This is one of currently only three known contact zones between "rhenanus"- Willow Tit and "montanus"- Willow Tit in Switzerland. Normally,  "rhenanus" and "montanus" are quite clearly segregated by habitat and elevation. At this location however, "rhenanus" seems to be the dominant species in the habitat of "montanus".
